NAME
    df - report filesystem disk space usage

SYNOPSIS
    df [options] [file...]

DESCRIPTION
    Displays information about mounted filesystems including
    total space, used space, and mount points.

    Note: Values are simulated for the virtual filesystem.

OPTIONS
    -h              Human-readable sizes (1024 base)
    -H              Human-readable sizes (1000 base)
    -T              Show filesystem type
    -i              Show inode information
    -a              Include pseudo-filesystems
    -l              Local filesystems only
    -t <type>       Show only filesystems of type
    -x <type>       Exclude filesystems of type
    --total         Produce a grand total

FILESYSTEMS
    Virtual filesystem mounts:
    /           Root filesystem (vfs)
    /tmp        Temporary storage (tmpfs)
    /api        API data storage (api)
    /home       User home directories (vfs)
    /proc       Process information (proc)

EXAMPLES
    df
        Show all mounted filesystems

    df -h
        Human-readable output

    df -Th
        Include filesystem type

    df -h /api/data
        Show filesystem for path

    df --total
        Include grand total

OUTPUT
    Filesystem  Size  Used  Avail  Use%  Mounted on

SEE ALSO
    du, mount
